This paper deals with multi-agent cooperation and the development of a shared lexicon, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks for the agents, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The analysis of the object-symbol mapping involves understanding the strategies used by the agents, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.LG (Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the behavior of the agents in response to changes in the environment, which falls under the category of neural networks (NE), making cs.NE the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with emergent behavior and the study of complex systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (SD), making cs.SD the fifth likely sub-category.
